body:
### expected behaviour
owncloud should display and handle all files and directories that it stores.

### actual behaviour
owncloud seemingly "forgets" files and directories at random. when the url of such forgotten files is entered manually, the files re-appear.

### steps to reproduce
1. upload data by either davfs2 mount, web interface, sync client
2. wait some time
3. use any of these methods to access the data again. something might be missing.
4. manually enter url of missing file / directory in browser: file / directory appears again.

### server configuration
operating system:
ubuntu 12.04

web server:
server version: apache/2.2.22 (ubuntu)
server built:   mar  8 2013 15:53:13

database:
mysql

php version:
php 5.3.10-1ubuntu3.6 with suhosin-patch (cli) (built: mar 11 2013 14:31:48) 
copyright (c) 1997-2012 the php group
zend engine v2.3.0, copyright (c) 1998-2012 zend technologies

owncloud version:
owncloud 5.0.8	(up to date)

### client configuration
browser:
chrome version 28.0.1500.71

operating system:
ubuntu 12.04
gnome shell 3.4

